\f0\b \cf0 Script modes\

\f1\b0 Mode 1: Manual\
You enter order decisions for each role every week.\
Mode 2: Rolling Optimization\
You enter customer demand each week, and the model automatically recommends orders that minimize cost.\

\f0\b You need to set 3 optimization controls:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}- Min base-stock target (weeks of demand) = 1 >>> Lowest target the optimizer can choose for any role.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}- Max base-stock target (weeks of demand) = 6 >>> Highest target the optimizer can choose for any role.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}- Look-ahead horizon (weeks) = 6 >>> Each week, the optimizer simulates candidate policies over the next 6 weeks and picks the one with the lowest total inventory + backlog cost.\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Then the model:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}    Computes the best near-term policy\
{\listtext	2.	}    Prints recommended order quantities for all roles\
{\listtext	3.	}    Applies those orders\
{\listtext	4.	}    Prints the weekly summary\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
